The paper deals with algorithms for stable matching and clustering in a geometric setting, specifically on a grid. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in solving the problem. Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely to be relevant.
